(secondQuint)Evaluation of Energy Expenditure, Body Composition and Recovery Rates in Children With Severe Acute Malnutrition.

 Objectives 1.

 To assess energy expenditure and body composition by stable isotope techniques in children with Severe Acute Malnutrition 2.

 To evaluate the potential usefulness of body composition assessment as a predictor of outcome in children with SAM, based on stable isotope technique and multi-frequency bioelectrical impedance analysis (BIA) Inclusion criteria - Parents of children of age 6 months to 3 years - Resident of study area Exclusion criteria - Children with congenital malformations - Chronic debilitating illnesses - Refusal by parents to enroll in study.

